Step to deploy strimzi kafka cluster with cruise control with nginx-ingress routing and certificates.

Apply a strimzi_0.48.yaml in your aks/eks/ etc
apply noodpool.yaml
crete a namespace if you want 
apply kafka-upgrade.yaml
apply cruis_control_depl_Svc.yaml
apply cruis_control_nginx_configmap.yaml
Lets apply ingress controller
apply nginx-ingress-deplyment.yaml
apply nginx-Ingress-Controller-Service
apply ingress-Service-Account.yaml
get the External ip of ingress controller using below commnad
kubectl get service ingress-nginx-controller -n ingress-nginx
prefered-domain-Ext_IP_Addred.sslip.io(Make sure convert . to - from your ip Ex: it should be cruise-control-20-235-174-214.sslip.io
│              │            │     │
│              │            │     └── sslip.io DNS service
│              │            └──────── Your NGINX Ingress IP (20.235.174.214)
│              └───────────────────── Dashes replace dots in IP
└──────────────────────────────────── Your custom subdomain name)
How sslip.io Works:
sslip.io is a magic DNS service that:

Resolves any subdomain containing an IP address to that IP

Works with any valid IP format (dots, dashes, or encoded)

No registration required - it's free and automatic

apply IngressClass.yaml
apply ingress-ClusterRole-RBAC.yaml
apply ingress-ClusterRoleBinding
apply ingress-role-rolebind.yaml
apply nginx-Role-Leader-Election.yaml
apply iingress-RoleBinding-Leader-Election.yaml
apply ingress-application.yaml

lets apply the certificates
apply cert-manager.crds.yaml
apply cert-manager.yaml
apply certificate-template.yaml
apply clusterissuer-letsencrypt-prod.yaml
apply ingress-with-tls.yaml

If you want to do it using Azure DNS then follow the below steps

# Create DNS Zone
az network dns zone create \
  --resource-group RG_AKS_Ishaq \
  --name your-domain.com
3. Get Ingress IP and Create DNS Record
# Get ingress external IP
INGRESS_IP=$(kubectl get service ingress-nginx-controller -n ingress-nginx -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].ip}')

# Create DNS A record
az network dns record-set a add-record \
  --resource-group RG_AKS_Ishaq \
  --zone-name your-domain.com \
  --record-set-name cruise-control \
  --ipv4-address $INGRESS_IP

check it 
nslookup cruise-control.your-domain.com

apply same host into the ingress-application and certificates file like certificate issue file
